Pipe Expansion Joints Market Overview
The global Pipe Expansion Joints Market was valued at approximately USD 1.2 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 1.7 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 5.5% from 2025 to 2030. The increasing demand for efficient piping systems across industries such as oil & gas, chemical, power generation, and water treatment is driving the market’s growth. The need for pipe expansion joints arises due to their ability to absorb thermal expansion and contraction in piping systems, ensuring the stability and longevity of pipelines. The growing infrastructure development and industrialization in emerging economies are further contributing to market expansion.

